EXPERIENCE

Dec 2021 - Present

Mentor

In my role as a Team Lead at GeeksforGeeks, I successfully managed a team of 10-15 professionals, collaborating on various tasks such as resolving student queries, developing problems, projects, and courses. Leveraging my expertise in Python, Networking, SQL, Databases, Data Security, Data Structures, and Data Science, I created comprehensive and practical courses catering to a diverse range of technical areas. Some of the courses I developed include Python Course, Python Crash Course, Python Project Course (beginner to advanced level), Python Ursina Project Course, C++ Course, and Database Management Course. Additionally, I curated question sets for coding competitions and data visualization courses, ensuring an engaging learning experience. As a mentor, I actively organized coding competitions and motivated students to explore various Python libraries like Pygame, Ursina, Tkinter, Sys, Pandas, Matplotlib, Numpy, and Pytorch. By doing so, I aimed to provide students with a holistic understanding of the Python language and its applications.Moreover, I expanded my scope by developing courses on HTML/CSS, JavaScript, and ReactJS, focusing on web development. These courses covered fundamental concepts, React component-based architecture, and HTML/CSS styling techniques, empowering students to build modern and dynamic web applications.Throughout my tenure, my dedication to delivering a professional and enriching learning experience, coupled with my passion for teaching and comprehensive technical knowledge, enabled me to develop courses and contests of exceptional quality.

Aug 2020 - Dec 2021

Coding Instructor

As an instructor at Qin1, I had the opportunity to teach more than 400 classes to students ranging from 6 to 18 years old. During my tenure, I imparted knowledge on a variety of programming languages, including Java, Android App Development, Python, Scratch, and Android Studio. My focus on creating engaging and interactive lesson plans enabled me to receive an outstanding rating of 4.9 out of 5.0 from my students. I took great pride in ensuring that my students thoroughly understood the concepts that I taught them and could apply them in practical scenarios. In addition to my teaching responsibilities, I also mentored students who were preparing for coding competitions. My guidance helped them to sharpen their skills and perform exceptionally well in their respective contests. Overall, my experience at Qin1 allowed me to hone my skills as an instructor and enabled me to become a trusted authority in the field of programming education. My commitment to providing quality education has been reflected in the positive ratings that I received from my students.
